LOS ANGELES, CA -- Kobalt clients received top honors at the ASCAP (the American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers) 28th Annual Pop Music Awards, which was held at the Renaissance Hollywood Hotel in Los Angeles, CA.

The star-studded event, which was attended by hundreds of songwriters, recording artists and music industry leaders, paid special tribute to Kobalt clients Dr. Luke, Max Martin and Band of Horses and honored the songwriters and publishers behind some of today's most popular music. 

The top awards were presented to two Kobalt clients Lukasz &quot;Dr. Luke&quot; Gottwald and Max Martin, who were both named Songwriters of the Year. 

Kobalt client Band of Horses, which consists of Ben Bridwell, Creighton Barrett, Ryan Monroe, Tyler Ramsey and Bill Reynolds, received ASCAP's Vanguard Award which recognizes the impact of musical genres that help shape the future of American music. 

